### ============================================
### Custom Properties - APIs REST
### ============================================
###
### Gestiona custom properties de tu organización
### para agrupar y clasificar repositorios.
### ============================================

### Variables de configuración
@token = {{$dotenv GITHUB_TOKEN_DEMO_02}}
@org = {{$dotenv GITHUB_ORG}}
@baseUrl = https://api.github.com
@apiVersion = 2022-11-28

### =========================================
### 📋 PASO 1: Consultar el esquema existente
### =========================================

### Listar todos los custom properties definidos en la org
GET {{baseUrl}}/orgs/{{org}}/properties/schema
Authorization: Bearer {{token}}
Accept: application/vnd.github+json
X-GitHub-Api-Version: {{apiVersion}}

### =========================================
### 🏗️ PASO 2: Crear custom properties
### =========================================

### Crear o actualizar custom properties en la org
### Este ejemplo crea 2 properties: application_type y mobile_platform
PATCH {{baseUrl}}/orgs/{{org}}/properties/schema
Authorization: Bearer {{token}}
Accept: application/vnd.github+json
X-GitHub-Api-Version: {{apiVersion}}
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "properties": [
    {
      "property_name": "application_type",
      "value_type": "single_select",
      "required": false,
      "description": "Tipo de aplicacion del repositorio",
      "allowed_values": [
        "mobile",
        "web",
        "desktop"
      ],
      "values_editable_by": "org_and_repo_actors"
    },
    {
      "property_name": "mobile_platform",
      "value_type": "single_select",
      "required": false,
      "description": "Plataforma de la app movil. Dejala vacia para repos web o desktop",
      "allowed_values": [
        "android",
        "ios"
      ],
      "values_editable_by": "org_and_repo_actors"
    }
  ]
}

### =========================================
### 🏷️ PASO 3: Asignar valores a repos
### =========================================

### Asignar custom properties a repos específicos (en lote)
### Ejemplo: apps moviles Android
PATCH {{baseUrl}}/orgs/{{org}}/properties/values
Authorization: Bearer {{token}}
Accept: application/vnd.github+json
X-GitHub-Api-Version: {{apiVersion}}
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "repository_names": [
    "ghas-demo-mobile-android-kotlin",
    "ghas-demo-mobile-android-compose"
  ],
  "properties": [
    {
      "property_name": "application_type",
      "value": "mobile"
    },
    {
      "property_name": "mobile_platform",
      "value": "android"
    }
  ]
}

### Ejemplo: apps moviles iOS
PATCH {{baseUrl}}/orgs/{{org}}/properties/values
Authorization: Bearer {{token}}
Accept: application/vnd.github+json
X-GitHub-Api-Version: {{apiVersion}}
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "repository_names": [
    "ghas-demo-mobile-ios-swift",
    "ghas-demo-mobile-ios-swiftui"
  ],
  "properties": [
    {
      "property_name": "application_type",
      "value": "mobile"
    },
    {
      "property_name": "mobile_platform",
      "value": "ios"
    }
  ]
}

### Ejemplo: aplicaciones web
PATCH {{baseUrl}}/orgs/{{org}}/properties/values
Authorization: Bearer {{token}}
Accept: application/vnd.github+json
X-GitHub-Api-Version: {{apiVersion}}
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "repository_names": [
    "web-portal-clientes",
    "web-admin-console"
  ],
  "properties": [
    {
      "property_name": "application_type",
      "value": "web"
    },
    {
      "property_name": "mobile_platform",
      "value": null
    }
  ]
}

### Ejemplo: aplicaciones de escritorio
PATCH {{baseUrl}}/orgs/{{org}}/properties/values
Authorization: Bearer {{token}}
Accept: application/vnd.github+json
X-GitHub-Api-Version: {{apiVersion}}
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "repository_names": [
    "desktop-pos-app",
    "desktop-support-tool"
  ],
  "properties": [
    {
      "property_name": "application_type",
      "value": "desktop"
    },
    {
      "property_name": "mobile_platform",
      "value": null
    }
  ]
}

### =========================================
### 🔍 PASO 4: Consultar custom properties
### =========================================

### Listar TODOS los repos de la org con sus custom properties
GET {{baseUrl}}/orgs/{{org}}/properties/values?per_page=30
Authorization: Bearer {{token}}
Accept: application/vnd.github+json
X-GitHub-Api-Version: {{apiVersion}}

### Filtrar repos por un custom property específico
### Ejemplo: obtener solo repos mobile
GET {{baseUrl}}/orgs/{{org}}/properties/values?repository_query=props.application_type:mobile
Authorization: Bearer {{token}}
Accept: application/vnd.github+json
X-GitHub-Api-Version: {{apiVersion}}

### Filtrar por múltiples properties
### Ejemplo: repos mobile Android
GET {{baseUrl}}/orgs/{{org}}/properties/values?repository_query=props.application_type:mobile props.mobile_platform:android
Authorization: Bearer {{token}}
Accept: application/vnd.github+json
X-GitHub-Api-Version: {{apiVersion}}

### =========================================
### 📦 PASO 5: Consultar properties de un repo
### =========================================

### Obtener los custom properties de un repo específico
@repo = ghas-demo-mobile-android-kotlin
GET {{baseUrl}}/repos/{{org}}/{{repo}}/properties/values
Authorization: Bearer {{token}}
Accept: application/vnd.github+json
X-GitHub-Api-Version: {{apiVersion}}
